https://serverpilot.io/docs/how-to-use-ssh-public-key-authentication/
https://winscp.net/eng/docs/guide_public_key

1. Generate key pair on your local machine.
2. Set up server to accept the public key (winscp or putty have the functionality built in)
3. Save the location of the private key into the session that you load every time
4. You win!
